A java package is group of classes and interfaces 
which are related to one single module in the given project.

Package naming convention

package name is always written in all-lowercase.

package names are always written in reverse order of domain

 convention 1
  domain.appname.modulename
  com.gmail.inbox  

  convention 2
  domain.companyname.appname.modulename
  com.google.gmail.inbox

Data members and function members of a class present in 
different package can be accessed by two ways

1 .Using fully qualified class names 
2 .Using import statement

 A class name which is written with its package name is 
 called as fully qualified class name.
 